Package: xtcadfcoint
Type: Package
Title: Panel CADF Cointegration Test with Structural Breaks
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Muhammad", "Alkhalaf", email = "muhammedalkhalaf@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-2677-9246"))
Description: Implements the panel cointegration test with structural instabilities
    of Banerjee and Carrion-i-Silvestre (2025) <doi:10.1080/07350015.2024.2352073>.
    Tests the null hypothesis of no cointegration using cross-sectionally augmented
    Dickey-Fuller (CADF) regressions, accounting for common factors via the Common
    Correlated Effects (CCE) estimator and allowing for structural breaks in the
    cointegrating vector, factor loadings, and deterministic components.
    Provides panel CIPS statistics under multiple model specifications (constant,
    trend, level shifts, slope shifts) with automatic or fixed lag selection.
    Bootstrap critical value simulation is supported.
